<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7970c9c5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1266"><num value="1266">§ 1266.</num><heading> Hearing before report of criminal violation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Before any violation of this chapter is reported by the Commission to any United States attorney for institution of a criminal proceeding, the person against whom such proceeding is contemplated shall be given appropriate notice and an opportunity to present his views, either orally or in writing, with regard to such contemplated proceeding.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7970c9c6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/86/613/s7">Pub. L. 86–613, § 7</ref>, <date date="1960-07-12">July 12, 1960</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/74/377">74 Stat. 377</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/110/314/tII/s204/b/4/B">Pub. L. 110–314, title II, § 204(b)(4)(B)</ref>, <date date="2008-08-14">Aug. 14, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/3041">122 Stat. 3041</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
